Cody tried another swing, but his aim was spoiled as Lulu darted between him and the lichen. "You are not helping," he said
through gritted teeth. He shuddered at the thought of explaining to his wife how Lulu had been consumed by ambulatory fauna
or -- worse yet -- sliced by Cody's own farming implement. That thought gave rise to another, though. "Pole sickle, lichen --
is this a theme?" Cody wondered. "If so, who is doing the farming?"
